cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on improving textual entailment models by leveraging external knowledge bases, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks and knowledge lookup modules, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in the process of verifying sub-facts against the structured knowledge base. Finally, the paper's focus on improving performance on a specific task (Science Entailment) suggests that it could also fall under the sub-category of neural engineering (cs.NE).
